Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a #medium pot{} with a 
tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve 
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Lay the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%g} onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} then season with @Curry Powder{1%sachet}, 
@salt{to taste} and @Peper{to taste}.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. 
> Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due 
> to packaging used to keep it fresh.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

Trim the tip of the @Broccoli{1%unit}. Cut head into small florets and stem 
into 2cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the chicken has ~{15%minutes} left to cook, remove the tray from the oven 
and pop the broccoli next to the chicken.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste} 
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer and cook for ~{10-15%minutes}.

== Stir-Fried Baby Corn ==

Meanwhile, halve the @Baby Corn{150%g} lengthways.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the baby corn and stir-fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. 
Season with @salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Transfer the baby corn to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

== Spicy Teriyaki Glaze ==

When the chicken has ~{5%minutes} of cooking time left, return the pan to 
medium-high heat.

Add the @Teriyaki Sauce{1%sachet}, @Gochujang Paste{1%sachet}, and a knob of 
@Butter{to taste} to the pan along with @Water{25%ml} (double for 4p).

Allow the sauce to warm through, adding another splash more water if you feel 
it's too thick.

Once roasted, add the chicken to the pan and turn to coat evenly in the glaze.

== To Serve ==

Transfer your spicy teriyaki chicken to your plates.

Spoon the remaining sauce over the chicken.

Serve with rice, baby corn and roasted broccoli alongside.